    "15": {
      "answer": "When you store and process PII, the biggest risk is unnecessary exposure of internal traffic. If microservices communicate over public endpoints, you increase the attack chances. A typical setup would be private subnets for microservices + private connectivity to managed services, with only a controlled entry point (like an API) exposed publicly.",
      "answered_at": "2026-04-12T16:07:23.947Z",
      "date": "2026-04-12",
      "time": "18:07:23"
    },
    "16": {
      "answer": "In a serverless database setup, the cloud provider owns the entire server layer, so they are responsible for the operating system: provisioning it, securing it... You don’t access or maintain that OS at all.  Dependency management is therefore split: the provider manages all dependencies on the database side , while you manage application-side dependencies",
      "answered_at": "2026-04-12T16:07:23.947Z",
      "date": "2026-04-12",
      "time": "18:07:23"
    }
  }
